# data-models-relationships

Core Data Models:

1. Treatment Facility Model (Importance: 95/100)
- Specialized categorization system:
  - Facility types (sober living, detox, residential, outpatient, IOP/PHP)
  - Population served (men, women, coed, LGBTQ+)
  - Insurance acceptance tracking (MediCal, Medicare, Private, RBH)
  - Verification status workflow
- Relationships:
  - Many-to-many with Insurance Providers
  - One-to-many with Facility Reviews
  - Many-to-many with Treatment Programs

2. Legal Case Model (Importance: 90/100)
- Case type classification:
  - Custody workflows
  - Expungement processes
  - Document requirements by case type
- Milestone tracking system
- Relationships:
  - One-to-many with Case Documents
  - Many-to-many with Legal Resources
  - One-to-one with Case Status

3. Community Resource Model (Importance: 85/100)
- Multi-layer categorization:
  - Service types (food, shelter, medical)
  - Availability patterns
  - Population restrictions
  - Verification status
- Trust scoring system
- Relationships:
  - Many-to-many with Service Categories
  - One-to-many with Resource Updates
  - Many-to-many with Verification Records

4. Recovery Meeting Model (Importance: 80/100)
- Meeting type classification:
  - Program affiliations (AA/NA/CMA/SMART)
  - Format types (in-person/online/hybrid)
  - Language support tracking
- Anonymous attendance system
- Relationships:
  - Many-to-many with Locations
  - One-to-many with Meeting Times
  - Many-to-many with Special Requirements

5. MediCal Provider Model (Importance: 85/100)
- Provider verification system
- Specialty categorization
- Network affiliation tracking
- Multi-language support
- Relationships:
  - Many-to-many with Insurance Plans
  - One-to-many with Provider Locations
  - Many-to-many with Specialties

Key Verification Workflows:
- Community-driven resource status verification
- Treatment facility accreditation tracking
- Provider network validation
- Resource trust scoring system
- Anonymous reporting mechanism

